elease is much too late for me.  <br>
<br>
I have friends on Tunare and a strong commitment to my guild, not to mention over 130 days (that’s 3,120 hours) invested in my primary character. If I were starting today I’d definitely make my character on Firiona Vie, but when I read how it is hard to find groups and what a pain the TLC is, I’m not particularly motivated to make the switch.<br>
<br>
About the TLC, I have to question whether this really promotes role-playing or just creates a needless hurdle for players.  How RP is it for you to know in advance what items you’ll need before even being given a quest because you know the creatures that have those quest items will /consider green when you’re capable of completing the quest?  So everyone in Norrath is supposed to be clairvoyant?  <br>
<br>
I don’t know how many of you have played DAoC, but their questing system is so much better.  Yes, DAoC has a TLC but it’s not a problem for quests because you get quest items even off of creatures that don’t give experience…and you don’t receive quest items unless you’ve already initiated the quest.  In DAoC you don’t have to store several bags of quest items in the bank, wondering what the heck they’re for, before finally finding the spoiler information on some website like you do in EQ.<br>
<br>
So yes, having to leave friends and guildmates is the primary reason, time invested in character obtaining experience, skills, and items a secondary reason, with the TLC and the lack of people to play with being a tertiary reason for not changing servers.<br>
<br>
*EDIT*<br>
<br>
I wanted to add that I don't feel threatened by the existence of an official RP server, nor do I feel like I'm any less an RPer because I don't play on it.  It sounds like you guys have a lot of fun, but I have fun on my regular server, too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Oh, and shame on that troll for enslaving a poor druid!  If I were her I'd port you to Surefall Glade and let those Jaggedpine Treefolk teach you a thing or three! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
